S. my last to you was on the 17 curitt to which please to be referred the packetts N.19
are att dover by this time according to what mr. vallego wrott mee, I hope itt
will be quickley with you & prove to content I have sold our bale of bayes
so faile not to gett itt schipped aboard pinder, as also the others I in ordered beside
please to provide 20 bayes more of 40 leweight with 10 a 12 of 33 a 34 et to be
an othed bale & dispatched as soone as possible for have non to sell now must
trouble you for £100:- because to day amto pay yd bill of ⅓ july & have no mony
to spare to remitt mr. Cole, for itt must go that way, & he is vere urgent for
yd brothers de sea sed rest so please to accept my bill of this day 2 uso ton
Cole or order att 35 & note according to yd acctt when itt faills due you
may redraw itt for I must even that concerne with him though I have yott
Leverall tanding out, inorim hope to see you here faddamss whish

S. in answer to yd of 58: past. sence here inclosed my bill for £100: att
2 uso att the charge of m. Abram vivian att 35:5 which please to
note according I should have remitted itt in an other bill, butt must pay
thisday yd of July for yd acctt. & so could not pass itt I do not doubt
butt that in 2 months heme all will be receaved so I shall not faile
to remitt you the rest for I do my atmost endeavour tocleare that
acctt., I desire that the £80:- on mr. Daiel vvian be advested, & that
the soonert the better, for if possible I shall make saddanly an end fothe
rest, whilst I am well informed that m. Depeyster had never order

that wee may have what is due depend on you discretion remaind
